description: Some gangsters are trying to steal an oil plantation. Kid has something to say about that.

Kid oversees a murder, but is unable to stop it from happening (because of Mr. Keepers foolishness)! The murdered is Simon Kane, and the victim his partner in a law firm, Mr. Emory! Kane wants the whole firm for himself.

The murderer stages a young man, Jimmy Conroy, for it. His third partner in the law firm. and Kid has to save the boy. He summons two historical figures, but they can`t help much. The case seems to be airtight.

The trial is had, Daniel Webster has tried to help but has failed and Kid has been kidnapped (and clubbed unconscious) by a bunch of thugs!

He wakes up just in time, sends for a legendary figure to beat up the hoodlums guarding him, and goes back to the courthouse.

How can he save Conroy? Easy. He simply summons the now dead Mr. Emory to testify of his own murder! Case solved.
It`s Kid Eternity vs. a 40`s gangster with Attila The Hun! Without his powers!

Kid calls Gerald Cronson, one of the greatest crooks of the 1920`s, to catch an escaped convict. Mr. Keeper tells Kid that it`s a mistake.

Kid believes him, and calls him back to eternity.

But...without neither knowing, he said it in a sound proof room, so the word didn`t reach Eternity.

Which means that Cronson is on the loose, and teams up with the convict! Troubles are born out of this.

George Washington of three ages vs. a criminal coveting for a formula for high explosives!

Jonesy-strip.

Her Highness and Silk.

Sir Roger.

Betty Bates busting crime.

Bob and Swab in Hawaii.

Big Feller becomes a boxer.
A traditional alien attack (well, except that this is the first time Kid Eternity faces one)! Seemingly unstoppable mold! Louis Pasteur!

A young man fresh out of the university, goes to Brazil, to find a forgotten world on a mountain! It`s filled with creatures that were thought to be absolutely extinct. Dangerous creatures! Kid Eternity, Mr. Keeper and a bunch of great mythological and historical figures must help the lad not get killed in the magnificent location!

Also a two page prose story featuring Kid and Keep, in what they visit the dawn of mankind.

Also has the other regular strips.

Kid and Keep meet (and fight against) the man who lived a million years, due to a mistake done in Heaven!

Also a prose stroy starring the pair, and many other comics.

Rip Van Winkle, George Washington and Tecumseh appear on the cover, not in the stories.

description: "Sympathy for the Devil". Kilroy, a mysterious spirit of vengeance crosses paths with a young boy in rural Georgia but he soon discovers that he cannot keep his promise to keep the boy safe.

"Reflections" - Part One. As a washed up beat reporter searches for the mysterious legendary person known as Kilroy, a being that seems to appear during the worst atrocities committed by man throughout the 20th century and the messages left behind. While Kilroy himself tracks down a serial of young girls to deliver his own brand of vengeance.
name: Reflections Part One

description: "Reflections" - Part Two. Kilroy visits an seemingly innocent old man living out his remaining days in a retirement home but one who holds a deep secret of atrocities committed duing World War II. In the process Kilroy rescues an infant from a burning building and leaves folks with more questions then answers. The reporter looking into the Kilroy phenomenon receives a phone call from the old man who gives him further insight into who or what Kilory is.
name: Reflections Part Two

description: "Reflections" - Part Three. An aging World War II veteran recounts the day of meeting Kilroy during the liberation of a Nazi concentration camp as an investigative reporter follows up on another lead that takes him to a priest with a strange story to tell about crossing paths with the mysterious being known as Kilroy.
name: Reflections Part Three
